Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '315'. Name Ieron. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX L248.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (162)
